 290     /**                                                                                                  
 291      * Retrieve the child {@link DatabaseReference references} from an specific parent which equals to thðŸ”µ
 292      * references retrieved from another query. Which allow to make a "where" clause on a no relational tðŸ”µ
 293      * <p>                                                                                               
 294      * Example:                                                                                          
 295      * DatabaseReference from = reference.child("Tweets");                                               
 296      * Query where = reference.child("favorited").child(userA);                                          
 297      * requestFilteredReferenceKeys(from, where).subscribe...                                            
 298      * <p>                                                                                               
 299      * This last method will return the key references(/tweets/tweetId) which the userA mark as favoritedðŸ”µ
 300      * With the given list we can work together with {@link RxFirebaseDatabase#observeMultipleSingleValueðŸ”µ
 301      * to retrieve the Datasnapshots from the desired {@link DatabaseReference} based on other {@link DatðŸ”µ
 302      *                                                                                                   
 303      * @param from     base reference where you want to retrieve the original references.                
 304      * @param whereRef reference that you use as a filter to create your from references.                
 305      * @return a {@link Maybe} which contain the list of the given DatabaseReferences.                   
 306      */                                                                                                  
 307     @NonNull                                                                                             
 308    public static Maybe<DatabaseReference[]> requestFilteredReferenceKeys(@NonNull final DatabaseReferenceðŸ”µ
 309                                                                          @NonNull Query whereRef) {      
 310       return observeSingleValueEvent(whereRef, new Function<DataSnapshot, DatabaseReference[]>() {       
 311          @Override                                                                                       
 312          public DatabaseReference[] apply(@NonNull DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) throws Exception {         
 313             int childrenCount = (int) dataSnapshot.getChildrenCount();                                   
 314             DatabaseReference[] filterRefs = new DatabaseReference[childrenCount];                       
 315             final Iterator<DataSnapshot> iterator = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator();               
 316             for (int i = 0; i < childrenCount; i++) {                                                    
 317                filterRefs[i] = from.child(iterator.next().getKey());                                     
 318             }                                                                                            
 319             return filterRefs;                                                                           
 320          }                                                                                               
 321       });                                                                                                
 322    }

  38    * Listener for changes in te data at the given query location.                                        
  39    *                                                                                                     
  40    * @param query    reference represents a particular location in your Database and can be used for readðŸ”µ
  41    * @param strategy {@link BackpressureStrategy} associated to this {@link Flowable}                    
  42    * @return a {@link Flowable} which emits when a value of the database change in the given query.

  44   @NonNull                                                                                               
  45   public static Flowable<DataSnapshot> observeValueEvent(@NonNull                                        
  46   final Query query, @NonNull                                                                            
  47   BackpressureStrategy strategy) {                                                                       
  48     return Flowable.create(new FlowableOnSubscribe<DataSnapshot>() {                                     
  49       @Override                                                                                          
  50       public void subscribe(final FlowableEmitter<DataSnapshot> emitter) throws Exception {              
  51         final ValueEventListener valueEventListener = new ValueEventListener() {                         
  52           @Override                                                                                      
  53           public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {                                          
  54             if (dataSnapshot.exists()) {                                                                 
  55               emitter.onNext(dataSnapshot);                                                              
  56             } else {                                                                                     
  57               emitter.onComplete();                                                                      
  58             }                                                                                            
  59           }                                                                                              
  60                                                                                                          
  61           @Override                                                                                      
  62           public void onCancelled(final DatabaseError error) {                                           
  63             if (!emitter.isCancelled()) {                                                                
  64               emitter.onError(new RxFirebaseDataException(error));                                       
  65             }                                                                                            
  66           }                                                                                              
  67         };                                                                                               
  68         emitter.setCancellable(new Cancellable() {                                                       
  69           @Override                                                                                      
  70           public void cancel() throws Exception {                                                        
  71             query.removeEventListener(valueEventListener);                                               
  72           }                                                                                              
  73         });                                                                                              
  74         query.addValueEventListener(valueEventListener);                                                 
  75       }                                                                                                  
  76     }, strategy);                                                                                        
  77   }

 113   /**                                                                                                    
 114    * Run a transaction on the data at this location. For more information on running transactions, see   
 115    *                                                                                                     
 116    * @param ref              reference represents a particular location in your database.                
 117    * @param fireLocalEvents  boolean which allow to receive calls of your transaction in your local devicðŸ”µ
 118    * @param transactionValue value of the transaction.                                                   
 119    * @return a {@link Single} which emits the final {@link DataSnapshot} value if the transaction successðŸ”µ
 120    */                                                                                                    
 121   @NonNull                                                                                               
 122   public static Single<DataSnapshot> runTransaction(@NonNull                                             
 123   final DatabaseReference ref, @NonNull                                                                  
 124   final boolean fireLocalEvents, @NonNull                                                                
 125   final long transactionValue) {                                                                         
 126     return Single.create(new SingleOnSubscribe<DataSnapshot>() {                                         
 127       @Override                                                                                          
 128       public void subscribe(final SingleEmitter emitter) throws Exception {                              
 129         ref.runTransaction(new Transaction.Handler() {                                                   
 130               @Override                                                                                  
 131               public Transaction.Result doTransaction(MutableData mutableData) {                         
 132                  Integer currentValue = mutableData.getValue(Integer.class);                             
 133                  if (currentValue == null) {                                                             
 134                     mutableData.setValue(transactionValue);                                              
 135                  } else {                                                                                
 136                     mutableData.setValue(currentValue + transactionValue);                               
 137                  }                                                                                       
 138                  return Transaction.success(mutableData);                                                
 139               }                                                                                          
 140                                                                                                          
 141           @Override                                                                                      
 142           public void onComplete(DatabaseError databaseError, boolean b, DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {    
 143             if ((databaseError != null) && (!emitter.isDisposed())) {                                    
 144               emitter.onError(new RxFirebaseDataException(databaseError));                               
 145             } else {                                                                                     
 146               emitter.onSuccess(dataSnapshot);                                                           
 147             }                                                                                            
 148           }                                                                                              
 149         }, fireLocalEvents);                                                                             
 150       }                                                                                                  
 151     });                                                                                                  
 152   }

 498 +                                                           @NonNull BackpressureStrategy strategy) {              
 499 +        return Flowable.create(new FlowableOnSubscribe<DataSnapshot>() {

 558 +    /**

 560 +     *                                                                                                            
 561 +     * @param ref              reference represents a particular location in your database.                       
 562 +     * @param fireLocalEvents  boolean which allow to receive calls of your transaction in your local device.

 565 +     */

 567 +    public static Single<DataSnapshot> runTransaction(@NonNull final DatabaseReference ref,                       
 568 +                                                      @NonNull final boolean fireLocalEvents,

 570 +        return Single.create(new SingleOnSubscribe<DataSnapshot>() {                                              
 571 +            @Override

 573 +                ref.runTransaction(new Transaction.Handler() {                                                    
 574 +                    @Override                                                                                     
 575 +                    public Transaction.Result doTransaction(MutableData mutableData) {                            
 576 +                        Integer currentValue = mutableData.getValue(Integer.class);                               
 577 +                        if (currentValue == null) {                                                               
 578 +                            mutableData.setValue(transactionValue);                                               
 579 +                        } else {                                                                                  
 580 +                            mutableData.setValue(currentValue + transactionValue);                                
 581 +                        }                                                                                         
 582 +                        return Transaction.success(mutableData);                                                  
 583 +                    }                                                                                             
 584 +                                                                                                                  
 585 +                    @Override

 587 +                        if (databaseError != null && !emitter.isDisposed()) {                                     
 588 +                            emitter.onError(new RxFirebaseDataException(databaseError));                          
 589 +                        } else {                                                                                  
 590 +                            emitter.onSuccess(dataSnapshot);                                                      
 591 +                        }                                                                                         
 592 +                    }                                                                                             
 593 +                }, fireLocalEvents);                                                                              
 594 +            }                                                                                                     
 595 +        });

 114     /**                                                                                                            
 115      * Run a transaction on the data at this location. For more information on running transactions, see           
 116      *                                                                                                             
 117      * @param ref              reference represents a particular location in your database.                        
 118      * @param fireLocalEvents  boolean which allow to receive calls of your transaction in your local device.      
 119      * @param transactionValue value of the transaction.                                                           
 120      * @return a {@link Single} which emits the final {@link DataSnapshot} value if the transaction success.       
 121      */                                                                                                            
 122     @NonNull                                                                                                       
 123     public static Single<DataSnapshot> runTransaction(@NonNull final DatabaseReference ref,                        
 124                                                       @NonNull final boolean fireLocalEvents,                      
 125                                                       @NonNull final long transactionValue) {                      
 126        return Single.create(new SingleOnSubscribe<DataSnapshot>() {                                                
 127           @Override public void subscribe(final SingleEmitter emitter) throws Exception {                          
 128              ref.runTransaction(new Transaction.Handler() {                                                        
 129                 @Override                                                                                          
 130                 public Transaction.Result doTransaction(MutableData mutableData) {                                 
 131                    Integer currentValue = mutableData.getValue(Integer.class);                                     
 132                    if (currentValue == null) {                                                                     
 133                       mutableData.setValue(transactionValue);                                                      
 134                    } else {                                                                                        
 135                       mutableData.setValue(currentValue + transactionValue);                                       
 136                    }                                                                                               
 137                    return Transaction.success(mutableData);                                                        
 138                 }                                                                                                  
 139                                                                                                                    
 140                 @Override                                                                                          
 141                 public void onComplete(DatabaseError databaseError, boolean b, DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {        
 142                    if (databaseError != null) {                                                                    
 143                       emitter.onError(new RxFirebaseDataException(databaseError));                                 
 144                    } else {                                                                                        
 145                       emitter.onSuccess(dataSnapshot);                                                             
 146                    }                                                                                               
 147                 }                                                                                                  
 148              }, fireLocalEvents);                                                                                  
 149           }                                                                                                        
 150        });                                                                                                         
 151     }

 214     @NonNull                                                                                                       
 215     public static Flowable<RxFirebaseChildEvent<DataSnapshot>> observeChildEvent(                                  
 216        @NonNull final Query query, @NonNull BackpressureStrategy strategy) {                                       
 217        return Flowable.create(new FlowableOnSubscribe<RxFirebaseChildEvent<DataSnapshot>>() {                      
 218           @Override                                                                                                
 219           public void subscribe(final FlowableEmitter<RxFirebaseChildEvent<DataSnapshot>> emitter) throws ExceptionðŸ”µ
 220              final ChildEventListener childEventListener = new ChildEventListener() {                              
 221                                                                                                                    
 222                 @Override                                                                                          
 223                 public void onChildAdded(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot, String previousChildName) {                    
 224                    emitter.onNext(                                                                                 
 225                       new RxFirebaseChildEvent<>(dataSnapshot.getKey(), dataSnapshot, previousChildName,           
 226                          RxFirebaseChildEvent.EventType.ADDED));                                                   
 227                 }                                                                                                  
 228                                                                                                                    
 229                 @Override                                                                                          
 230                 public void onChildChanged(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot, String previousChildName) {                  
 231                    emitter.onNext(                                                                                 
 232                       new RxFirebaseChildEvent<>(dataSnapshot.getKey(), dataSnapshot, previousChildName,           
 233                          RxFirebaseChildEvent.EventType.CHANGED));                                                 
 234                 }                                                                                                  
 235                                                                                                                    
 236                 @Override                                                                                          
 237                 public void onChildRemoved(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {                                            
 238                    emitter.onNext(new RxFirebaseChildEvent<>(dataSnapshot.getKey(), dataSnapshot,                  
 239                       RxFirebaseChildEvent.EventType.REMOVED));                                                    
 240                 }                                                                                                  
 241                                                                                                                    
 242                 @Override                                                                                          
 243                 public void onChildMoved(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot, String previousChildName) {                    
 244                    emitter.onNext(                                                                                 
 245                       new RxFirebaseChildEvent<>(dataSnapshot.getKey(), dataSnapshot, previousChildName,           
 246                          RxFirebaseChildEvent.EventType.MOVED));                                                   
 247                 }                                                                                                  
 248                                                                                                                    
 249                 @Override                                                                                          
 250                 public void onCancelled(DatabaseError error) {                                                     
 251                    emitter.onError(new RxFirebaseDataException(error));                                            
 252                 }                                                                                                  
 253              };                                                                                                    
 254              emitter.setCancellable(new Cancellable() {                                                            
 255                 @Override                                                                                          
 256                 public void cancel() throws Exception {                                                            
 257                    query.removeEventListener(childEventListener);                                                  
 258                 }                                                                                                  
 259              });                                                                                                   
 260              query.addChildEventListener(childEventListener);                                                      
 261                                                                                                                    
 262           }                                                                                                        
 263        }, strategy);                                                                                               
 264     }

 266     /**                                                                                                            
 267      * Method which retrieve a list of DataSnapshot from multiple {@link DatabaseReference}.                       
 268      *                                                                                                             
 269      * @param whereRefs array of {@link DatabaseReference references.}                                             
 270      * @return a {@link Flowable} which emmit {@link DataSnapshot} from the given queries.                         
 271      */                                                                                                            
 272     @NonNull                                                                                                       
 273     public static Flowable<DataSnapshot> observeMultipleSingleValueEvent(@NonNull DatabaseReference... whereRefs) {
 274        return Maybe.merge(Flowable.fromArray(whereRefs)                                                            
 275        .map(new Function<DatabaseReference, MaybeSource<? extends DataSnapshot>>() {                               
 276              @Override                                                                                             
 277              public MaybeSource<? extends DataSnapshot> apply(@NonNull DatabaseReference databaseReference) throws 
 278                    Exception {                                                                                     
 279                 return observeSingleValueEvent(databaseReference);                                                 
 280              }                                                                                                     
 281           })                                                                                                       
 282        );                                                                                                          
 283     }

 285     /**                                                                                                            
 286      * Retrieve the child {@link DatabaseReference references} from an specific parent which equals to the         
 287      * references retrieved from another query. Which allow to make a "where" clause on a no relational table.     
 288      * <p>                                                                                                         
 289      * Example:                                                                                                    
 290      * DatabaseReference from = reference.child("Tweets");                                                         
 291      * Query where = reference.child("favorited").child(userA);                                                    
 292      * requestFilteredReferenceKeys(from, where).subscribe...                                                      
 293      * <p>                                                                                                         
 294      * This last method will return the key references(/tweets/tweetId) which the userA mark as favorited.         
 295      * With the given list we can work together with {@link RxFirebaseDatabase#observeMultipleSingleValueEvent(DataðŸ”µ
 296      * to retrieve the Datasnapshots from the desired {@link DatabaseReference} based on other {@link DatabaseReferðŸ”µ
 297      *                                                                                                             
 298      * @param from     base reference where you want to retrieve the original references.                          
 299      * @param whereRef reference that you use as a filter to create your from references.                          
 300      * @return a {@link Maybe} which contain the list of the given DatabaseReferences.                             
 301      */                                                                                                            
 302     @NonNull                                                                                                       
 303     public static Maybe<DatabaseReference[]> requestFilteredReferenceKeys(@NonNull final DatabaseReference from,   
 304                                                                           @NonNull Query whereRef) {               
 305        return observeSingleValueEvent(whereRef, new Function<DataSnapshot, DatabaseReference[]>() {                
 306           @Override                                                                                                
 307           public DatabaseReference[] apply(@NonNull DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) throws Exception {                  
 308              int childrenCount = (int) dataSnapshot.getChildrenCount();                                            
 309              DatabaseReference[] filterRefs = new DatabaseReference[childrenCount];                                
 310              final Iterator<DataSnapshot> iterator = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator();                        
 311              for (int i = 0; i < childrenCount; i++) {                                                             
 312                 filterRefs[i] = from.child(iterator.next().getKey());                                              
 313              }                                                                                                     
 314              return filterRefs;                                                                                    
 315           }                                                                                                        
 316        });                                                                                                         
 317     }
